================================================================================
Autotools build system
================================================================================

This document explains how to build SDLU with configure


================================================================================
Supported platforms
================================================================================

* GNU/Linux (Tested: Ubuntu, Linux Mint)
* Cygwin/MSYS (Tested)
* Mac OS X (Not tested, but should work)
* Raspberry Pi (Tested)
* iOS -- makefiles (see README-ios)


================================================================================
Features
================================================================================

+ Configure is a shell script -- no extra depencies to run it
+ Works better for UNIX platforms than CMake
+ Should be easy enough to port to other UNIX systems
+ Supports cygwin


================================================================================
Usage
================================================================================

Open a shell and type [assuming SDLU is at ~/sdlu]

    $ cd ~/sdlu
    $ ./configure; make; make install

To update configure, use 'bootstrap':

    $ cd ~/sdlu
    $ ./scripts/bootstrap

================================================================================
Options
================================================================================

For the full list of available options, run './configure --help'. Here are
described some of the most common options you will need:

* --prefix: Choose the location where the library will be installed
* --enable-cxx: Build the cxx interface
* --enable-debug: Build with debugging information
* --with-sdl-prefix: Prefix where SDL is installed


================================================================================
Finding frameworks (Mac OS X)
================================================================================

configure is unable to properly locate the SDL2 and SDL2_ttf frameworks under
Mac OS X. This means that if you use these frameworks and do not link to the
libraries directly, you should set the following environment variables:
(assuming the frameworks are installed in /Library/Frameworks)

    $ export SDL2_FRAMEWORK=/Library/Frameworks/SDL2.framework
    $ export SDL2_TTF_FRAMEWORK=/Library/Frameworks/SDL2_ttf.framework
    $ ./configure; make; make install


================================================================================
Notes for developers
================================================================================

If you already have an autotools build system for your project, and want to find
SDLU, place 'scripts/autotools/m4/sdlu.m4' along with the other *.m4 files, and
add the following in your configure.ac:

    AM_PATH_SDLU([2.1], have_sdlu=yes, have_sdlu=no)
    if test x$have_sdlu = xyes; then
        CFLAGS="$CFLAGS $SDLU_CFLAGS"
        LIBS="$CFLAGS $SDLU_LIBS"
    else
        ....
    fi

To complete the changes run aclocal and autoconf, or just 'autoreconf'


-- Aggelos Kolaitis
